>
  <main id="main"><header class="page-hero page-hero--image-right"><div class="container"><div class="breadcrumbs"><a href="index.html">Home</a> / <a href="host-institutions.html">Host Institutions</a> / Become a Host</div><span class="kicker">Host a Fellow</span><h1>Create a setting for consequential service</h1><p>US Fellows invites mission-driven institutions to define supported appointments grounded in public benefit, clear contribution, and responsible supervision.</p></div></header><nav class="anchor-nav anchor-nav--bar" aria-label="On this page"><div class="container"><a href="#process"><span>01</span>How it works</a><a href="#overview"><span>02</span>Overview</a><a href="#focus"><span>03</span>Areas of focus</a><a href="#principles"><span>04</span>Principles</a><a href="#next"><span>05</span>Next steps</a></div></nav><section class="section" id="process"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">From intent to practice</span><h2>Building a strong host relationship</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Good appointments begin before a Fellow arrives. Hosts clarify the work, establish support, and agree on what responsible completion looks like.</p></div><div class="process-stair"><article class="step"><h3>Propose</h3><p>Describe the mission, institutional need, likely work, intended benefit, and responsible owner. Here, attend to define the need: Identify the institutional challenge, public context, and why a fellowship contribution is appropriate now.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>Qualify</h3><p>Confirm organizational standing, supervision, resources, role clarity, and alignment with Society standards. Here, attend to name the work: Describe core responsibilities, expected outputs, working relationships, and realistic boundaries.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>Match and shape</h3><p>Align the opportunity with a Fellow&#x27;s capabilities and turn it into a realistic appointment plan. Here, attend to provide support: Assign a responsible supervisor and ensure access to the people, information, tools, and feedback required.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>Support and close</h3><p>Provide feedback throughout the work, review outcomes, and capture lessons at completion. Here, attend to plan for value: Clarify how the institution will use the work and what the Fellow should learn or carry forward.</p></article></div></div></section><section class="section thesis-opening" id="overview"><div class="container"><span class="thesis-index" aria-hidden="true">01</span><div class="prose"><span class="eyebrow">For Host Institutions</span><h2>Bring capable people into work that matters</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Host Institutions turn mission into a setting where a Fellow can contribute with context, supervision, access, and accountable purpose.</p><p>The strongest proposals begin with a real need rather than a generic request for talent. They explain why the work matters, what success would make possible, and who will support it.</p><p>Define the need establishes the point of entry; plan for value defines what should remain after the immediate work is complete.</p></div><blockquote>Define the need establishes the point of entry; plan for value defines what should remain after the immediate work is complete.</blockquote></div></section><section class="section section--mist" id="focus"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">The host relationship</span><h2>What a consequential host setting must provide</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Host Institutions turn mission into a setting where a Fellow can contribute with context, supervision, access, and accountable purpose.</p></div><div class="focus-bento"><article class="dimension-card"><span>01</span><LegacyIcon name="compass" /><h3>Define the need</h3><p>Identify the institutional challenge, public context, and why a fellowship contribution is appropriate now.</p></article><article class="dimension-card"><span>02</span><LegacyIcon name="institution" /><h3>Name the work</h3><p>Describe core responsibilities, expected outputs, working relationships, and realistic boundaries.</p></article><article class="dimension-card"><span>03</span><LegacyIcon name="lightbulb-o" /><h3>Provide support</h3><p>Assign a responsible supervisor and ensure access to the people, information, tools, and feedback required.</p></article><article class="dimension-card"><span>04</span><LegacyIcon name="handshake-o" /><h3>Plan for value</h3><p>Clarify how the institution will use the work and what the Fellow should learn or carry forward.</p></article></div></div></section><section class="section" id="principles"><div class="container principle-sidebar"><aside><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">Conditions for trust</span><h2>The responsibilities of a qualified host</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Responsible hosting requires a real need, capable supervision, and mutual clarity from the outset.</p></div></aside><div class="grid grid--3"><article class="card card--numbered"><span class="card__number">01</span><h3>A credible need</h3><p>The opportunity should respond to real institutional or public-interest work rather than create an ornamental role. In this context, consider define the need.</p></article><article class="card card--numbered"><span class="card__number">02</span><h3>Responsible support</h3><p>A Fellow needs a designated supervisor, appropriate access, timely feedback, and a safe working setting. In this context, consider name the work.</p></article><article class="card card--numbered"><span class="card__number">03</span><h3>Mutual value</h3><p>The appointment should respect the Fellow&#x27;s capabilities while producing useful value for the mission and institution. In this context, consider provide support.</p></article></div></div></section><section class="close-split" id="next"><div><div><h2>Shape an opportunity the Society can assess</h2><p>Begin with define the need, then define a contribution your capabilities or institution can support.</p></div><div class="actions"><a class="button button--gold" href="submit-opportunity.html">Submit an opportunity</a><a class="button button--outline" href="become-a-host.html">Become a Host</a></div></div><aside class="related-panel"><span class="eyebrow">Continue exploring</span><h3>Related pathways</h3><ul class="related-list"><li><a href="host-institutions.html">Host overview</a></li><li><a href="host-standards.html">Host standards</a></li><li><a href="appointment-model.html">Appointment model</a></li></ul></aside></section></main>

</BaseLayout>
